			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Actually, it is an ad hominem attack...distracting the discussion by insulting your opponent.  So...yes it is an insult...but it is also an attempt to excuse the audience from seriously considering Mr. Limbaugh's positions.  It is an attempt to shout down the discussion through the bandwagon fallacy:  you should believe as I do because everyone else does.
<br />

<br />
And that is what is going on towards Rush at the moment.  There are a lot of people who have managed to hide the general discontent with the current status of racial politics...and they are being outted by Rush for that bandwagonism.
<br />

<br />
A HEALTHY response, again, is found in the first two paragraphs of Selph's post.  Respond with facts and meaningful analysis.  An UNHEALTHY response is to call your opponent ignorant.
<br />

<br />
Wolen
<br />

<br />
EDIT:  "A healthy response ARE..." just didn't work...so changed it to "is found in".<span class="gensmall"></span>


